 the common cultural and aesthetic ground shared by writers, editors and critics across the ideological divides of the era.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aGerman literaturey20th centuryvPeriodicals. 0aGerman literaturey20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 4aDeutschland. 4aLiteraturgeschichte. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh1 aDavies, Peter, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aPhilpotts, Matthew, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Literary and Cultural Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110637854oZDB-23-GLC0 cprintz978311018113540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311090612740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110906127423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110906127/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-GLCc2000d2014